cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper deals with Natural Language Inference (NLI) and proposes new datasets and a novel attention mechanism to improve the understanding of entities and roles. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes modifications to existing NLI architectures, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The use of neural networks in NLI also suggests the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which is a popular technique in computer vision, suggesting the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
